I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve the API data first, as this is the first step in the workflow.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
  {
    "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
    "timeout": 30,
    "retry_count": 3,
    "options": {}
  }
</tool_call>

I'll use the data_processing_validator tool to validate the fetched data against a schema. Since we need a schema, I'll use a default schema for JSON data validation.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
  {
    "schema": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "data": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object"
          }
        }
      },
      "required": ["data"]
    },
    "data": {},
    "options": {}
  }
</tool_call>

Now that we've validated the data, the next step is to parse it for structured output. I'll use the data_processing_parser tool to process the validated data.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
  {
    "source": "data/input.json",
    "options": {
      "format": "json",
      "structure": "hierarchical"
    }
  }
</tool_call>
